obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34704)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34704&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Ancient Monuments`
  line `and Archaeological Sites and Remains Act, 1958.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1972, s. 33, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  line
  line `2. 15th October, 1959, vide notification No. S. O. 2307, dated 15th October, 1959, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34705)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34705&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "ancient monument" means any structure, erection or monument, or any tumulus or place`
  line `of interment, or any cave, rock-sculpture, inscription or monolith, which is of historical,`
  line `archaeological or artistic interest and which has been in existence for not less than one hundred`
  line `years, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the remains of an ancient monument,`
  line
  line `(ii) the site of an ancient monument,`
  line
  line `(iii) such portion of land adjoining the site of an ancient monument as may be required for`
  line `fencing or covering in or otherwise preserving such monument, and`
  line
  line `(iv) the means of access to, and convenient inspection of, an ancient monument;`
  line
  line `(b) "antiquity" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any coin, sculpture, manuscript, epigraph, or other work of art or craftsmanship,`
  line
  line `(ii) any article, object or thing detached from a building or cave,`
  line
  line `(iii) any article, object or thing illustrative of science, art, crafts, literature, religion,`
  line `customs, morals or politics in bygone ages,`
  line
  line `(iv) any article, object or thing of historical interest, and`
  line
  line `(v) any article, object or thing declared by the Central Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, to be an antiquity for the purposes of this Act,`
  line
  line `which has been in existence for not less than one hundred years;`
  line
  line `(c) "archaeological officer" means an officer of the Department of Archaeology of the`
  line `Government of India not lower in rank than Assistant Superintendent of Archaeology;`
  line
  line `(d) "archaeological site and remains" means any area which contains or is reasonably`
  line `believed to contain ruins or relics of historical or archaeological importance which have been in`
  line `existence for not less than one hundred years, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) such portion of land adjoining the area as may be required for fencing or covering in or`
  line `otherwise preserving it, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the means of access to, and convenient inspection of, the area;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) "Authority" means the National Monuments Authority constituted under section 20F;`
  line
  line `(db) "competent authority" means an officer not below the rank of Director of archaeology or`
  line `Commissioner of archaeology of the Central or State Government or equivalent rank, specified,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, as the competent authority by the Central Government to`
  line `perform functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `different competent authorities for the purpose of sections 20C, 20D and 20E;`
  line
  line `(dc) "construction" means any erection of a structure or a building, including any addition or`
  line `extension thereto either vertically or horizontally, but does not include any re-construction, repair`
  line `and renovation of an existing structure or building, or, construction, maintenance and cleansing of`
  line `drains and drainage works and of public latrines, urinals and similar conveniences, or, the`
  line `construction and maintenance of works meant for providing supply of water for public, or, the`
  line `construction or maintenance, extension, management for supply and distribution of electricity to`
  line `the public or provision for similar facilities for public;]`
  line
  line `(e) "Director-General" means the Director-General of Archaeology, and includes any officer`
  line `authorised by the Central Government to perform the duties of the Director-General;`
  line
  line `(f) "maintain", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, includes the fencing,`
  line `covering in, repairing, restoring and cleansing of a protected monument, and the doing of any act`
  line `which may be necessary for the purpose of preserving a protected monument or of securing`
  line `convenient access thereto;`
  line
  line `(g) "owner" includes"`
  line
  line `(i) a joint owner invested with powers of management on behalf of himself and other joint`
  line `owners and the successor-in-title of any such owner; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any manager or trustee exercising powers of management and the successor-in-office`
  line `of any such manager or trustee;`
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^2[(ha) "prohibited area" means any area specified or declared to be a prohibited area under`
  line `section 20A;]`
  line
  line `(i) "protected area" means any archaeological site and remains which is declared to be of`
  line `national importance by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "protected monument" means an ancient monument which is declared to be of national`
  line `importance by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `^2[(k) "re-construction" means any erection of a structure or building to its pre-existing`
  line `structure, having the same horizontal and vertical limits;`
  line
  line `(l) "regulated area" means any area specified or declared under section 20B;`
  line
  line `(m) "repair and renovation" means alterations to a pre-existing structure or building, but shall`
  line `not include construction or re-construction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (34706)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to any law not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34706&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. [Construction of references to any law not in force in the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir^*.]--Omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws)`
  line `Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of`
  line `Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E),`
  line `dated (23-10-2020).].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 52 of 1972, s. 33 (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34707)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Certain ancient monuments, etc., deemed to be of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34707&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `All ancient and`
  line `historical monuments and all archaeological sites and remains which have been declared by`
  line `the Ancient and Historical Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Declaration of`
  line `National Importance) Act, 1951 (71 of 1951), or by section 126 of the States Reorganisation`
  line `Act, 1956 (37 of 1956), to be of national importance shall be deemed to be ancient and historical`
  line `monuments or archaeological sites and remains declared to be of national importance for the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34708)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to declare ancient monuments, etc., to be of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34708&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Central Government is of opinion that any ancient monument or`
  line `archaeological site and remains not included in section 3 is of national importance, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, give two months notice of its intention to declare such ancient`
  line `monument or archaeological site and remains to be of national importance; and a copy of every such`
  line `notification shall be affixed in a conspicuous place near the monument or site and remains, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person interested in any such ancient monument or archaeological site and remains may,`
  line `within two months after the issue of the notification, object to the declaration of the monument, or the`
  line `archaeological site and remains, to be of national importance.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of the said period of two months, the Central Government may, after`
  line `considering the objections, if any, received by it, declare by notification in the Official Gazette, the`
  line `ancient monument or the archaeological site and remains, as the case may be, to be of national`
  line importance.
  line
  line `(4) A notification published under sub-section (3) shall, unless and until it is withdrawn, be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the fact that the ancient monument or the archaeological site and remains to`
  line `which it relates is of national importance for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (34765)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 6
  title `Categorisation and classification in respect of ancient monuments or archaeological sites and remains declared as of national importance under sections 3 and 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34765&sectionno=4A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Categorisation and classification in respect of ancient monuments or archaeological`
  line `sites and remains declared as of national importance under sections 3 and 4.--(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, on the recommendation of the Authority, prescribe categories in respect`
  line `of ancient monuments or archaeological sites and remains declared as of national importance under`
  line `sections 3 and 4, and while prescribing such categories it shall have regard to the historical,`
  line `archaeological and architectural value and such other factors as may be relevant for the purpose of`
  line `such categorisation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, on the recommendation of the Authority, classify all the`
  line `ancient monuments or archaeological sites and remains declared as of national importance under`
  line `sections 3 and 4, in accordance with the categories prescribed under sub-section (1) and thereafter`
  line `make the same available to the public and exhibit the same on its website and also in such other`
  line `manner as it may deem fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34710)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Acquisition of rights in a protected monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34710&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General may, with the`
  line `sanction of the Central Government, purchase, or take a lease of, or accept a gift or bequest of, any`
  line `protected monument.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a protected monument is without an owner, the Director-General may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, assume the guardianship of the monument.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner of any protected monument may, by written instrument, constitute the`
  line `Director-General the guardian of the monument, and the Director-General may, with the sanction of`
  line `the Central Government, accept such guardianship.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Director-General has accepted the guardianship of a monument under`
  line `sub-section (3), the owner shall, except as expressly provided in this Act, have the same estate, right,`
  line `title and interest in and to the monument as if the Director-General had not been constituted a`
  line `guardian thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) When the Director-General has accepted the guardianship of a monument under`
  line `sub-section (3), the provisions of this Act relating to agreements executed under section 6 shall apply`
  line `to the written to agreements executed under the said sub-section.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in this section shall affect the use of any protected monument for customary religious`
  line observances.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34711)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Preservation of protected monument by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34711&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector, when so directed`
  line `by the Central Government, shall propose to the owner of a protected monument to enter into an`
  line `agreement with the Central Government within a specified period for the maintenance of the`
  line monument.
  line
  line `(2) An agreement under this section may provide for all or any of the following matters,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the maintenance of the monument;`
  line
  line `(b) the custody of the monument and the duties of any person who may be employed to`
  line `watch it;`
  line
  line `(c) the restriction of the owner's right--`
  line
  line `(i) to use the monument for any purpose,`
  line
  line `(ii) to charge any fee for entry into, or inspection of, the monument,`
  line
  line `(iii) to destroy, remove, alter or deface the monument, or`
  line
  line `(iv) to build on or near the site of the monument;`
  line
  line `(d) the facilities of access to be permitted to the public or any section thereof or to`
  line `archaeological officers or to persons deputed by the owner or any archaeological officer or the`
  line `Collector to inspect or maintain the monument;`
  line
  line `(e) the notice to be given to the Central Government in case the land on which the monument`
  line `is situated or any adjoining land is offered for sale by the owner, and the right to be reserved to`
  line `the Central Government to purchase such land, or any specified portion of such land, at its market`
  line value;
  line
  line `(f) the payment of any expenses incurred by the owner or by the Central Government in`
  line `connection with the maintenance of the monument;`
  line
  line `(g) the proprietary or other rights which are to vest in the Central Government in respect of`
  line `the monument when any expenses are incurred by the Central Government in connection with the`
  line `maintenance of the monument;`
  line
  line `(h) the appointment of an authority to decide any dispute arising out of the agreement; and`
  line
  line `(i) any matter connected with the maintenance of the monument which is a proper subject of`
  line `agreement between the owner and the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government or the owner may, at any time after the expiration of three years from`
  line `the date of execution of an agreement under this section, terminate it on giving six months notice in`
  line `writing to the other party:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the agreement is terminated by the owner, he shall pay to the Central`
  line `Government the expenses, if any, incurred by it on the maintenance of the monument during the five`
  line `years immediately preceding the termination of the agreement or, if the agreement has been in force`
  line `for a shorter period, during the period the agreement was in force.`
  line
  line `(4) An agreement under this section shall be binding on any person claiming to be the owner of`
  line `the monument to which it relates, from, through or under a party by whom or on whose behalf the`
  line `agreement was executed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34712)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Owners under disability or not in possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34712&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the owner of a protected monument is`
  line `unable, by reason of infancy or other disability, to act for himself, the son legally competent to act on`
  line `his behalf may exercise the powers conferred upon an owner by section 6.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of village property, the headman or other village officer exercising powers of`
  line `management over such property may exercise the powers conferred upon an owner by section 6.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to empower any person not being of the same religion`
  line `as the person on whose behalf he is acting to make or execute an agreement relating to a protected`
  line `monument which or any part of which is periodically used for the religious worship or observances of`
  line `that religion.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34713)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Application of endowment to repair a protected monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34713&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any owner or other`
  line `person competent to enter into an agreement under section 6 for the maintenance of a protected`
  line `monument refuses or fails to enter into such an agreement, and if any endowment has been created for`
  line `the purpose of keeping such monument in repair or for that purpose among others, the Central`
  line `Government may institute a suit in the court of the district judge, or, if the estimated cost of repairing`
  line `the monument does not exceed one thousand rupees, may make an application to the district judge, for`
  line `the proper application of such endowment or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) On the hearing of an application under sub-section (1), the district judge may summon and`
  line `examine the owner and any person whose evidence appears to him necessary and may pass an order`
  line `for the proper application of the endowment or of any part thereof, and any such order may be`
  line `executed as if it were a decree of a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34714)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 11
  title `Failure or refusal to enter into an agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34714&sectionno=9&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any owner or other person competent`
  line `to enter into an agreement under section 6 for the maintenance of a protected monument refuses or`
  line `fails to enter into such an agreement, the Central Government may make an order providing for all or`
  line `any of the matters specified in sub-section (2) of section 6 and such order shall be binding on the`
  line `owner or such other person and on every person claiming title to the monument from, through or`
  line `under, the owner or such other person.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order made under sub-section (1) provides that the monument shall be maintained`
  line `by the owner or other person competent to enter into an agreement, all reasonable expenses for the`
  line `maintenance of the monument shall be payable by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No order under sub-section (1) shall be made unless the owner or other person has been given`
  line `an opportunity of making a representation in writing against the proposed order.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34715)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make order prohibiting contravention of agreement under section 6.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34715&sectionno=10&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `Director-General apprehends that the owner or occupier of a protected monument intends to destroy,`
  line `remove, alter, deface, imperil or misuse the monument or to build on or near the site thereof in`
  line `contravention of the terms of an agreement under section 6, the Director-General may, after giving the`
  line `owner or occupier an opportunity of making a representation in writing, make an order prohibiting`
  line `any such contravention of the agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such opportunity may be given in any case where the Director-General, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded, is satisfied that it is not expedient or practicable to do so.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order under this section may appeal to the Central Government`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed and the decision of the Central`
  line `Government shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34716)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 13
  title `Enforcement of agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34716&sectionno=11&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an owner or other person who is bound by an agreement`
  line `for the maintenance of a monument under section 6 refuses or fails within such reasonable time as the`
  line `Director-General may fix, to do any act which in the opinion of the Director-General is necessary for`
  line `the maintenance of the monument, the Director-General may authorise any person to do any such act,`
  line `and the owner or other person shall be liable to pay the expenses of doing any such act or such portion`
  line `of the expenses as the owner may be liable to pay under the agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises regarding the amount of expenses payable by the owner or other person`
  line `under sub-section (1), it shall be referred to the Central Government whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34767)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 14
  title `Purchasers at certain sales and persons claiming through owner bound by instrument executed by owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34767&sectionno=12&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every person who purchases, at a sale for arrears of land revenue or any other`
  line `public demand, any land on which is situated a monument in respect of which any instrument has`
  line `been executed by the owner for the time being under section 5 or section 6, and every person claiming`
  line `any title to a monument from, through or under, an owner who executed any such instrument, shall be`
  line `bound by such instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34718)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Acquisition of protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34718&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government apprehends`
  line `that a protected monument is in danger of being destroyed, injured, misused, or allowed to fall`
  line `into decay, it may acquire the protected monument under the provisions of the Land Acquisition`
  line `Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), as if the maintenance of the protected monument were a public purpose within`
  line `the meaning of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34719)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Maintenance of certain protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34719&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `maintain every monument which has been acquired under section 13 or in respect of which any of the`
  line `rights mentioned in section 5 have been acquired.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Director-General has assumed the guardianship of a monument under section 5, he`
  line `shall, for the purpose of maintaining such monument, have access to the monument at all reasonable`
  line `times, by himself and by his agents, subordinates and workmen, for the purpose of inspecting the`
  line `monument and for the purpose of bringing such materials and doing such acts as he may consider`
  line `necessary or desirable for the maintenance thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34720)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Voluntary contributions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34720&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Director-General may receive voluntary contributions`
  line `towards the cost of maintaining a protected monument and may give orders as to the management and`
  line `application of any funds so received by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contribution received under this section shall be applied to any purpose other`
  line `than the purpose for which it was contributed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34721)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of place of worship from misuse, pollution or desecration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34721&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A protected`
  line `monument maintained by the Central Government under this Act which is a place of worship or`
  line `shrine shall not be used for any purpose inconsistent with its character.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Government has acquired a protected monument under section 13, or where`
  line `the Director-General has purchased, or taken a lease or accepted a gift or bequest or assumed`
  line `guardianship of, a protected monument under section 5, and such monument or any part thereof is`
  line `used for religious worship or observances by any community, the Collector shall make due provision`
  line `for the protection of such monument or part thereof, from pollution or desecration--`
  line
  line `(a) by prohibiting the entry therein, except in accordance with the conditions prescribed with`
  line `the concurrence of the persons, if any, in religious charge of the said monument or part thereof, of`
  line `any person not entitled so to enter by the religious usages of the community by which the`
  line `monument or part thereof is used, or`
  line
  line `(b) by taking such other action as he may think necessary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34722)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Relinquishment of Government rights in a monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34722&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `With the sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, the Director-General may,--`
  line
  line `(a) where rights have been acquired by the Director-General in respect of any monument`
  line `under this Act by virtue of any sale, lease, gift or will, relinquish, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, the rights so acquired to the person who would for the time being be the owner of the`
  line `monument if such rights had not been acquired; or`
  line
  line `(b) relinquish any guardianship of a monument which he has assumed under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34723)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right of access to protected monuments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34723&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made under this Act, the`
  line `public shall have a right of access to any protected monument.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34724)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Restrictions on enjoyment of property rights in protected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34724&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person, including`
  line `the owner or occupier of a protected area, shall construct any building within the protected area or`
  line `carry on any mining, quarrying, excavating, blasting or any operation of a like nature in such area, or`
  line `utilise such area or any part thereof in any other manner without the permission of the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to prohibit the use of any such area or`
  line `part thereof for purposes of cultivation if such cultivation does not involve the digging of not more`
  line `than one foot of soil from the surface.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order, direct that any building constructed by any person`
  line `within a protected area in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be removed within a`
  line `specified period and, if the person refuses or fails to comply with the order, the Collector may cause`
  line `the building to be removed and the person shall be liable to pay the cost of such removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34725)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to acquire a protected area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34725&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government is of opinion that any`
  line `protected area contains an ancient monument or antiquities of national interest and value, it may`
  line `acquire such area under the provisions of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), as if the`
  line `acquisition were for a public purpose within the meaning of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (34766)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 23
  title `Declaration of prohibited area and carrying out public work or other works in prohibited area`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34766&sectionno=20A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Declaration of prohibited area and carrying out public work or other works in`
  line `prohibited area.--Every area, beginning at the limit of the protected area or the protected monument,`
  line `as the case may be, and extending to a distance of one hundred metres in all directions shall be the`
  line `prohibited area in respect of such protected area or protected monument:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Authority, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify an area more than one hundred metres to be the prohibited`
  line `area having regard to the classification of any protected monument or protected area, as the case may`
  line `be, under section 4A.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in section 20C, no person, other than an archaeological officer,`
  line `shall carry out any construction in any prohibited area.`
  line
  line `(3) In a case where the Central Government or the Director-General, as the case may be, is`
  line `satisfied that--`
  line
  line `(a) it is necessary or expedient for carrying out such public work or any project essential to`
  line `the public; or`
  line
  line `(b) such other work or project, in its opinion, shall not have any substantial adverse impact on`
  line `the preservation, safety, security of, or, access to, the monument or its immediate surrounding,`
  line
  line `it or he may, notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), in exceptional cases and having`
  line `regard to the public interest, by order and for reasons to be recorded in writing, permit, such public`
  line `work or project essential to the public or other constructions, to be carried out in a prohibited area:`
  line
  line `Provided that any area near any protected monument or its adjoining area declared, during the`
  line `period beginning on or after the 16th day of June, 1992 but ending before the date on which the`
  line `Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment and Validation) Bill, 2010,`
  line `receives the assent of the President, as a prohibited area in respect of such protected monument, shall`
  line `be deemed to be the prohibited area declared in respect of that protected monument in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act and any permission or licence granted by the Central Government or`
  line `the Director-General, as the case may be, for the construction within the prohibited area on the basis`
  line `of the recommendation of the Expert Advisory Committee, shall be deemed to have been validly`
  line `granted in accordance with the provisions of this Act, as if this section had been in force at all`
  line `material times:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply to any permission granted,`
  line `subsequent to the completion of construction or re-construction of any building or structure in any`
  line `prohibited area in pursuance of the notification of the Government of India in the Department of`
  line `Culture (Archaeological Survey of India) number S.O. 1764, dated the 16th June, 1992 issued under`
  line `rule 34 of the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains Rules, 1959, or, without`
  line `having obtained the recommendations of the Committee constituted in pursuance of the order of the`
  line `Government of India number 24/22/2006-M, dated the 20th July, 2006 (subsequently referred to as`
  line `the Expert Advisory Committee in orders dated the 27th August, 2008 and the 5th May, 2009).]`
  line
  line `^2[(4) No permission, referred to in sub-section (3), including carrying out any public work or`
  line `project essential to the public or other constructions, shall be granted in any prohibited area on and`
  line `after the date on which the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment`
  line `and Validation) Bill, 2010 receives the assent of the President.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 4 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_b:
  sectionId (34727)
  sectionNo 20B
  orderNo 24
  title `Declaration of regulated area in respect of every protected monument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34727&sectionno=20B&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[20B. Declaration of regulated area in respect of every protected monument.--Every area,`
  line `beginning at the limit of prohibited area in respect of every ancient monument and archaeological site`
  line `and remains, declared as of national importance under sections 3 and 4 and extending to a distance of`
  line `two hundred metres in all directions shall be the regulated area in respect of every ancient monument`
  line `and archaeological site and remains:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify an area`
  line `more than two hundred metres to be the regulated area having regard to the classification of any`
  line `protected monument or protected area, as the case may be, under section 4A:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any area near any protected monument or its adjoining area declared, during`
  line `the period beginning on or after the 16th day of June, 1992 but ending before the date on which the`
  line `Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment and Validation) Bill, 2010,`
  line `receives the assent of the President, as a regulated area in respect of such protected monument, shall`
  line `be deemed to be the regulated area declared in respect of that protected monument in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act and any permission or licence granted for construction in such regulated`
  line `area shall, be deemed to have been validly granted in accordance with the provisions of this Act, as if`
  line `this section had been in force at all material times.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_c:
  sectionId (34768)
  sectionNo 20C
  orderNo 25
  title `Application for repair or renovation in prohibited area, or construction or re-construction or repair or renovation in regulated area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34768&sectionno=20C&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[20C. Application for repair or renovation in prohibited area, or construction or`
  line `re-construction or repair or renovation in regulated area.--(1) Any person, who owns any`
  line `building or structure, which existed in a prohibited area before the 16th day of June, 1992, or, which`
  line `had been subsequently constructed with the approval of the Director-General and desires to carry out`
  line `any repair or renovation of such building or structure, may make an application to the competent`
  line `authority for carrying out such repair or renovation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, who owns or possesses any building or structure or land in any regulated area,`
  line `and desires to carry out any construction or re-construction or repair or renovation of such building or`
  line `structure on such land, as the case may be, may make an application to the competent authority for`
  line `carrying out construction or re-construction or repair or renovation, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_d:
  sectionId (34729)
  sectionNo 20D
  orderNo 26
  title `Grant of permission by competent authority within regulated area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34729&sectionno=20D&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[20D. Grant of permission by competent authority within regulated area.--(1) Every`
  line `application for grant of permission under section 20C of this Act shall be made to the competent`
  line `authority in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority shall, within fifteen days of the receipt of the application, forward the`
  line `same to the Authority to consider and intimate impact of such construction (including the impact of`
  line `large-scale development project, public project and project essential to the public) having regard to`
  line `the heritage bye-laws relating to the concerned protected monument or protected area, as the case`
  line `may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may prescribe the category of applications in respect of`
  line `which the permission may be granted under this sub-section and the application which shall be`
  line `referred to the Authority for its recommendations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority shall, within two months from the date of receipt of application under`
  line `sub-section (2), intimate to the competent authority impact of such construction (including the impact`
  line `of large-scale development project, public project and project essential to the public).`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority shall, within one month of the receipt of intimation from the`
  line `Authority under sub-section (3), either grant permission or refuse the same as so recommended by the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(5) The recommendations of the Authority shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) In case the competent authority refuses to grant permission under this section, it shall, by order`
  line `in writing, after giving an opportunity to the concerned person, intimate such refusal within three`
  line `months from the date of receipt of the application to the applicant, the Central Government and the`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(7) If the competent authority, after grant of the permission under sub-section (4) and during the`
  line `carrying out of the repair or renovation work or re-construction of building or construction referred to`
  line `in that sub-section, is of the opinion (on the basis of material in his possession or otherwise) that such`
  line `repair or renovation work or re-construction of building or construction is likely to have an adverse`
  line `impact on the preservation, safety, security or access to the monument considerably, it may refer the`
  line `same to the Authority for its recommendations and if so recommended, withdraw the permission`
  line `granted under sub-section (4) if so required:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, in exceptional cases, with the approval of the`
  line `Authority grant permission to the applicant referred to in sub-section (2) of section 20C until the`
  line `heritage bye-laws have been prepared under sub-section (1) of section 20E and published under`
  line `sub-section (7) of that section.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government, or the Director-General, as the case may be, shall exhibit, on their`
  line `website, all the permissions granted or refused under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_e:
  sectionId (34730)
  sectionNo 20E
  orderNo 27
  title `Heritage bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34730&sectionno=20E&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[20E. Heritage bye-laws.--(1) The competent authority, in consultation with Indian`
  line `National Trust for Arts and Cultural Heritage, being a trust registered under the Indian Trusts`
  line `Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), or such other expert heritage bodies as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government, shall prepare heritage bye-laws in respect of each protected monument and protected`
  line area.
  line
  line `(2) The heritage bye-laws referred to in sub-section (1) shall, in addition to such matters as may`
  line `be prescribed, include matters relating to heritage controls such as elevations, facades, drainage`
  line `systems, roads and service infrastructure (including electric poles, water and sewer pipelines).`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, by rules, specify the manner of preparation of detailed site`
  line `plans in respect of each protected area or protected monument or prohibited area or regulated area, the`
  line `time within which such heritage bye-laws shall be prepared and particulars to be included in each`
  line `such heritage bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority for the purpose of preparation of detailed site plans and heritage`
  line `bye-laws may appoint such number of experts or consultants as it may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) A copy of each of the heritage bye-laws prepared under sub-section (1) shall be forwarded to`
  line `the Authority for its approval.`
  line
  line `(6) A copy of the heritage bye-laws as approved by the Authority under sub-section (5) shall be`
  line `laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(7) Each heritage bye-laws shall, be made available by the competent authority to the public, by`
  line `exhibiting the same on its website and also in such other manner as it may deem fit, immediately after`
  line `laying the same before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_f:
  sectionId (34731)
  sectionNo 20F
  orderNo 28
  title `Constitution of National Monuments Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34731&sectionno=20F&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[20F. Constitution of National Monuments Authority.--(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute an Authority to be called as the National Monuments`
  line Authority.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall consist of,--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, on whole-time basis, to be appointed by the President, having proven`
  line `experience and expertise in the fields of archaeology, country and town planning, architecture,`
  line `heritage, conservation-architecture or law;`
  line
  line `(b) such number of members not exceeding five whole-time members and five part-time`
  line `members to be appointed, on the recommendation of the Selection Committee referred to in`
  line `section 20G, by the Central Government, having proven experience and expertise in the fields of`
  line `archaeology, country and town planning, architecture, heritage, conservation-architecture or law;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director-General as member, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The tenure of the whole-time Chairperson or every whole-time member and every part-time`
  line `member, of the Authority shall be three years from the date on which he assumes office as such and`
  line `shall not be eligible for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that, save as otherwise provided in clause (c) of sub-section (2), any person who has`
  line `held any post in the Archaeological Survey of India or in the Ministry of Culture of the Government`
  line `of India or a State Government or has not been found fit to be considered for being appointed to any`
  line `such post shall, not be eligible to be appointed as the Chairperson or a member of the Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any person, who had either been granted a permission or licence or refused`
  line `any such permission or refused grant of a licence or any person or any of his relative having any`
  line `interest in a prohibited area or a regulated area shall not be eligible to be appointed as a Chairperson`
  line `or member.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "relative" means--`
  line
  line `(i) spouse of the Chairperson or member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) brother or sister of the Chairperson or member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(iii) brother or sister of the spouse of the Chairperson or member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(iv) brother or sister of either of the parents of the Chairperson or member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(v) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the Chairperson or member of the Authority;`
  line
  line `(vi) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the Chairperson or member of the`
  line Authority;
  line
  line `(vii) spouse of the person referred to in clauses (ii) to (vi);`
  line
  line `(4) An officer, not below the rank of Joint Secretary to the Government of India, shall be the`
  line `Member Secretary of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall provide such number of officers and other employees as may be`
  line `necessary for discharge of functions by the Authority under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_g:
  sectionId (34732)
  sectionNo 20G
  orderNo 29
  title `Selection Committee for selection of members of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34732&sectionno=20G&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[20G. Selection Committee for`
  line `selection of members of Authority.--(1) Every whole-time`
  line `member and every part-time member of the Authority shall be selected by a Selection Committee`
  line `consisting of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Cabinet Secretary--Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary in the Ministry of Culture--member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary in the Ministry of Urban development--member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) three experts, having proven experience and expertise in the fields of archaeology,`
  line `architecture, heritage or conservation-architecture to be nominated by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Selection Committee referred to in sub-section (1) shall regulate its own procedure for the`
  line `purposes of selecting whole-time members and part-time members of the Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_h:
  sectionId (34733)
  sectionNo 20H
  orderNo 30
  title `Salary, allowances and meetings of Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34733&sectionno=20H&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[20H. Salary, allowances and meetings of Authority.--(1) The salaries and allowances payable`
  line `to the whole-time Chairperson and whole-time members, and the other terms and conditions of their`
  line `service or fees or allowances payable to the part-time members, of the Authority shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the whole-time Chairperson and whole-time members shall be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall regulate its own procedure for the purposes of holding its meetings`
  line `(including quorum of such meetings) and granting permissions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) All the decisions of the Authority shall be published in such manner as it may decide and also`
  line `on its own website and on the website of the Central Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_i:
  sectionId (34769)
  sectionNo 20-I
  orderNo 31
  title `Functions and powers of Authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34769&sectionno=20-I&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[20-I. Functions and powers of Authority.--(1) The Authority shall exercise or discharge the`
  line `following powers or functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) make recommendations to the Central Government for grading and classifying protected`
  line `monuments and protected areas declared as of national importance under sections 3 and 4, before`
  line `the commencement of the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains`
  line `(Amendment and Validation) Act, 2010 (10 of 2010);`
  line
  line `(b) make recommendations to the Central Government for grading and classifying protected`
  line `monuments and protected areas which may be declared after the commencement of the`
  line `Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment and Validation)`
  line `Act, 2010 (10 of 2010), as of national importance under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) oversee the working of the competent authorities;.`
  line
  line `(d) to suggest measures for implementation of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) to consider the impact of large-scale developmental projects, including public projects and`
  line `projects essential to the public which may be proposed in the regulated areas and make`
  line `recommendations in respect thereof to the competent authority;`
  line
  line `(f) to make recommendations to the competent authority for grant of permission.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority shall, for the purpose of discharging functions under this Act, have the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while trying`
  line `a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_j:
  sectionId (34734)
  sectionNo 20J
  orderNo 32
  title `Removal of Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34734&sectionno=20J&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[20J. Removal of Chairperson and members.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 20F, the President in the case of the Chairperson and the Central`
  line `Government in the case of whole-time member and part-time member may, by order, remove from`
  line `office, the Chairperson or any such member of the Authority, if he--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as Chairperson or member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interests as is likely to affect prejudicially his`
  line `functions; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or any member of the Authority shall not be removed under clauses (d)`
  line `and (e) of sub-section (1) unless he has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the`
  line matter.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_k:
  sectionId (34735)
  sectionNo 20K
  orderNo 33
  title `Restriction on future employment by Chairperson and members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34735&sectionno=20K&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[20K. Restriction on future employment by Chairperson and members.--On ceasing to hold`
  line `office, the Chairperson or whole-time member of the Authority, as the case may be, shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of this Act, be ineligible, for a period of five years from the date on which they cease to`
  line `hold office, for further employment (including as consultant or expert or otherwise) in any institution,`
  line `agency or organisation of any nature mainly dealing with archaeology, country and town planning,`
  line `architecture, heritage and conservation-architecture or whose matters had been before the Chairperson`
  line `or such member.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_l:
  sectionId (34736)
  sectionNo 20L
  orderNo 34
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34736&sectionno=20L&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[20L. Power of Central Government to issue directions to Authority.--(1) Without prejudice`
  line `to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the Authority shall, in exercise of its powers or the discharge`
  line `of its functions under this Act, be bound by such directions on question of policy, other than those`
  line `relating to technical and administrative matters, as the Central Government may give in writing to it`
  line `from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its`
  line `views before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government, whether a question is one of policy or not, shall be`
  line final.]
obj_root_law_sections_20_m:
  sectionId (34737)
  sectionNo 20M
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions to competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34737&sectionno=20M&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[20M. Power of Central Government to issue directions to competent authority.--Without`
  line `prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this Act, the competent authority shall, in exercise of its`
  line `powers or the discharge of its functions under this Act, be bound by such directions, as the Central`
  line `Government may give in writing to it from time to time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_n:
  sectionId (34738)
  sectionNo 20N
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_n_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34738&sectionno=20N&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[20N. Power of Central Government to supersede Authority.--(1) If, at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion,--`
  line
  line `(a) that, on account of circumstances beyond the control of the Authority, it is unable to`
  line `discharge the functions or perform the duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Authority has persistently defaulted in complying with any direction given by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions or performance of the`
  line `duties imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the`
  line `financial position of the Authority or the administration of the Authority has suffered; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Authority for such`
  line `period, not exceeding six months, as may be specified in the notification and appoint a person or`
  line `persons as the President may direct to exercise powers and discharge functions under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing any such notification, the Central Government shall give a reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the Authority to make representations against the proposed supersession and shall`
  line `consider the representations, if any, of the Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Authority,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairperson and all other whole-time members and part-time members shall, as from`
  line `the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Authority shall, until the Authority is reconstituted`
  line `under sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by the person or persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(c) all properties owned or controlled by the Authority shall, until the Authority is`
  line `reconstituted under sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On or before the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (1), the Central Government shall reconstitute the Authority by a fresh appointment`
  line `of its Chairperson and other whole-time members and part-time members and in such case any person`
  line `who had vacated his office under clause (a) of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be disqualified,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 20F for reappointment for the remaining period.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a copy of the notification issued under sub-section (1)`
  line `and a full report of any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament at the earliest.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_o:
  sectionId (34770)
  sectionNo 20-O
  orderNo 37
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34770&sectionno=20-O&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[20-O. Bar of jurisdiction of civil court.--No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any`
  line `matter which the Authority is empowered by or under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be`
  line `granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of`
  line `any power conferred by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_p:
  sectionId (34739)
  sectionNo 20P
  orderNo 38
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34739&sectionno=20P&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[20P. Annual report.--(1) The Authority shall prepare once in every year, in such form and at`
  line `such time as may be prescribed by the Central Government, an annual report giving full description of`
  line `all the activities of the Authority for the previous year.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the report received under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_q:
  sectionId (34740)
  sectionNo 20Q
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_q_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34740&sectionno=20Q&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_20_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[20Q. Power to call for information.--Where the Central Government considers it expedient so`
  line `to do, it may, by order in writing call upon the Authority or the competent authority, as the case may`
  line `be, to furnish in writing such information, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, relating to`
  line `its affairs as the Central Government may require.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34741)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 40
  title `Excavations in protected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34741&sectionno=21&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `An archaeological officer or an officer authorised by him`
  line `in this behalf or any person holding a licence granted in this behalf under this Act (hereinafter referred`
  line `to as the licensee) may, after giving notice in writing to the Collector and the owner, enter upon and`
  line `make excavations in any protected area.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34742)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 41
  title `Excavations in areas other than protected areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34742&sectionno=22&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where an archaeological officer has`
  line `reason to believe that any area not being a protected area contains ruins or relies of historical or`
  line `archaeological importance, he or an officer authorised by him in this behalf may, after giving notice in`
  line `writing to the Collector and the owner, enter upon and make excavations in the area.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34743)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 42
  title `Compulsory purchase of antiquities, etc., discovered during excavation operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34743&sectionno=23&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, as a result of any excavations made in any area under section 21 or`
  line `section 22, any antiquities are discovered, the archaeological officer or the licensee, as the case may`
  line `be, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) as soon as practicable, examine such antiquities and submit a report to the Central`
  line `Government in such manner and containing such particulars as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) at the conclusion of the excavation operations, give notice in writing to the owner of the`
  line `land from which such antiquities have been discovered, of the nature of such antiquities.`
  line
  line `(2) Until an order for the ^1[compulsory acquisition] of any such antiquities is made under`
  line `sub-section (3), the archaeological officer or the licensee, as the case may be, shall keep them in such`
  line `safe custody as he may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of a report under sub-section (1), the Central Government may make an order for`
  line `the ^2[compulsory acquisition of any such antiquities].`
  line
  line `(4) When an order for the ^1[compulsory acquisition] of any antiquities is made under`
  line `sub-section (3), such antiquities shall rest in the Central Government with effect from the date of the`
  line order.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 52 of 1972, s. 33, for "compulsory purchase" (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for "compulsory purchase of any such antiquities at their market value" (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34744)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 43
  title `Excavations, etc., for archaeological purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34744&sectionno=24&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `No State Government shall undertake or`
  line `authorise any person to undertake any excavation or other like operation for archaeological purposes`
  line `in any area which is not a protected area except with the previous approval of the Central Government`
  line `and in accordance with such rules or directions, if any, as the Central Government may make or give`
  line `in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34745)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power of Central Government to control moving of antiquities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34745&sectionno=25&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central`
  line `Government considers that any antiquities or class of antiquities ought not to be moved from the place`
  line `where they are without the sanction of the Central Government, the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any such antiquity or any class of such antiquities shall`
  line `not be moved except with the written permission of the Director-General.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for permission under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and contain such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order refusing permission may appeal to the Central Government`
  line `whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34746)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 45
  title `Purchase of antiquities by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34746&sectionno=26&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government`
  line `apprehends that any antiquity mentioned in a notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 25 is`
  line `in danger of being destroyed, removed, injured, misused or allowed to fall into decay or is of opinion`
  line `that, by reason of its historical or archaeological importance, it is desirable to preserve such antiquity`
  line `in a public place, the Central Government may make an order for the ^1[compulsory acquisition of such`
  line `antiquity] and the Collector shall thereupon give notice to the owner of the antiquity ^2[to be acquired].`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice of ^3[compulsory acquisition] is issued under sub-section (1) in respect of any`
  line `antiquity, such antiquity shall vest in the Central Government with effect from the date of the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) The power of ^3[compulsory acquisition] given by this section shall not extend to any image or`
  line `symbol actually used for bona fide religious observances.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for "compulsory purchase of such antiquity at its market value" (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for "to be purchased" (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 52 of 1972, s. 33, for "compulsory purchase" (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34747)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 46
  title `Compensation for loss or damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34747&sectionno=27&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any owner or occupier of land who has sustained any`
  line `loss or damage or any diminution of profits from the land by reason of any entry on, or excavations in,`
  line `such land or the exercise of any other power conferred by this Act shall be paid compensation by the`
  line `Central Government for such loss, damage or diminution of profits.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34748)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 47
  title `Assessment of market value or compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 33, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 5-4-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34748&sectionno=28&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The market value of any property`
  line `which the Central Government is empowered to purchase at such value under this Act or the`
  line `compensation to be paid by the Central Government in respect of anything done under this Act`
  line `shall, where any dispute arises in respect of such market value or compensation, be ascertained in`
  line `the manner provided in sections 3, 5, 8 to 34, 45 to 47, 51 and 52 of the Land Acquisition`
  line `Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), so far as they can be made applicable:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when making an enquiry under the said Land Acquisition Act, the Collector shall`
  line `be assisted by two assessors, one of whom shall be a competent person nominated by the Central`
  line `Government and one a person nominated by the owner, or, in case the owner fails to nominate an`
  line `assessor within such reasonable time as may be fixed by the Collector in this behalf, by the Collector.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) For every antiquity in respect of which an order for compulsory acquisition has been`
  line `made under sub-section (3) of section 23 or under sub-section (1) of section 26, there shall be paid`
  line `compensation and the provisions of sections 20 and 22 of the Antiquities and Art Treasures`
  line `Act, 1972 (52 of 1972) shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to the determination and payment of`
  line `such compensation as they apply in relation to the determination and payment of compensation for`
  line `any antiquity or art treasure compulsorily acquired under section 19 of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34749)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 48
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34749&sectionno=29&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that any powers conferred on it by or under this Act shall, subject to such conditions as`
  line `may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government, or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or authority subordinate to the State Government,`
  line
  line `as may be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (34750)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 49
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34750&sectionno=30&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(i) destroys, removes, injures, alters, defaces, imperils or misuses a protected monument, or`
  line
  line `(ii) being the owner or occupier of a protected monument, contravenes an order made under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9 or under sub-section (1) of section 10, or`
  line
  line `(iii) removes from a protected monument any sculpture carving, image, bas-relief, inscription,`
  line `or other like object, or`
  line
  line `(iv) does any act in contravention of sub-section (1) of section 19,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with ^1[imprisonment`
  line `which may extend to two years], or with ^2[fine which may extend to one lakh rupees], or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who moves any antiquity in contravention of a notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25 shall be punishable with ^3[imprisonment which may extend to two years`
  line `or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both]; and the court convicting a person of`
  line `any such contravention may by order direct such person to restore the antiquity to the place from`
  line `which it was moved.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 8, for "imprisonment which may extend to three months" (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "fine which may extend to five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "fine which may extend to five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (34751)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 50
  title `Punishment for construction, etc., in prohibited area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34751&sectionno=30A&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Punishment for construction, etc., in prohibited area.--Whoever raises, on and after`
  line `the date on which the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment and`
  line `Validation) Bill, 2010, receives the assent of the President, any construction in the prohibited area,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment not exceeding two years or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `lakh rupees or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b:
  sectionId (34752)
  sectionNo 30B
  orderNo 51
  title `Punishment for construction, etc., in regulated area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34752&sectionno=30B&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[30B. Punishment for construction, etc., in regulated area.--Whoever raises, on and after the`
  line `date on which the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Sites and Remains (Amendment and`
  line `Validation) Bill, 2010, receives the assent of the President, any construction in the regulated area`
  line `without the previous permission of the competent authority or in contravention of the permission`
  line `granted by the competent authority, shall be punishable with imprisonment not exceeding two years or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_c:
  sectionId (34753)
  sectionNo 30C
  orderNo 52
  title `Offences by officers of Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34753&sectionno=30C&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_30_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[30C. Offences by officers of Government.--If any officer of the Central Government enters into`
  line `or acquiesces in any agreement to do, abstains from doing, permits, conceals or connives at any act or`
  line `thing whereby any construction or re-construction takes place in a prohibited area or regulated area,`
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (34754)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 53
  title `Jurisdiction to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34754&sectionno=31&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a presidency magistrate or a`
  line `magistrate of the first class shall try any offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (34755)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 54
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34755&sectionno=32&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), an offence under clause (i) or clause (iii) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 30, shall be deemed to be a cognizable offence within the meaning of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (34756)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 55
  title `Special provision regarding fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34756&sectionno=33&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 32 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), it shall be lawful for any magistrate of the first class`
  line `specially empowered by the State Government in this behalf and for any presidency magistrate to pass`
  line `a sentence of fine exceeding two thousand rupees on any person convicted of an offence which under`
  line `this Act is punishable with fine exceeding two thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (34757)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 56
  title `Recovery of amounts due to the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34757&sectionno=34&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any amount due to the Government from`
  line `any person under this Act may, on a certificate issued by the Director-General or an archaeological`
  line `officer authorised by him in this behalf be recovered in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (34758)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 57
  title `Ancient monuments, etc., which have ceased to be of national importance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34758&sectionno=35&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `If the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion that any ancient and historical monument or archaeological site and remains`
  line `declared to be of national importance by or under this Act has ceased to be of national importance, it`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the ancient and historical monument or`
  line `archaeological site and remains, as the case may be, has ceased to be of national importance for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35_a:
  sectionId (34759)
  sectionNo 35A
  orderNo 58
  title `Obligation to survey the protected prohibited area and regulated areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 10 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34759&sectionno=35A&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_35_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[35A. Obligation to survey the protected prohibited area and regulated areas.--(1) The`
  line `Director-General shall, within such time as may be specified by the Central Government, conduct a`
  line `survey or cause survey to be conducted in respect of all prohibited areas and regulated areas for the`
  line `purpose of detailed site plans.`
  line
  line `(2) A report in respect of such survey referred to in sub-section (1) shall be forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government and to the Authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_b:
  sectionId (34760)
  sectionNo 35B
  orderNo 59
  title `Identification of unauthorised constructions on or after 16th June, 1992.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 10 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34760&sectionno=35B&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_35_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[35B. Identification of unauthorised constructions on or after 16th June, 1992.--(1) The`
  line `Director-General shall, within such time as may be specified by the Central Government, identify`
  line `or cause to be identified, all constructions (of whatever nature) made on and after the 16th day of`
  line `June, 1992 in all prohibited areas and regulated areas and, thereafter, submit from time to time a`
  line `report in respect thereof to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General shall, for the purposes of sub-section (1), have the power to call for`
  line `information from the local bodies and other authorities.]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (34761)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power to correct mistakes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34761&sectionno=36&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any clerical mistake, patent error or error arising from`
  line `accidental slip or omission in the description of any ancient monument or archaeological site and`
  line `remains declared to be of national importance by or under this Act may, at any time, be corrected by`
  line `the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (34762)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 61
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34762&sectionno=37&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `No suit for compensation and no criminal`
  line `proceeding shall lie against any public servant in respect of any act done or in good faith intended to`
  line `be done in the exercise of any power conferred by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (34763)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power to make rule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34763&sectionno=38&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules for carrying out the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the prohibition or regulation by licensing or otherwise of mining, quarrying, excavating`
  line `blasting or any operation of a like nature near a protected monument or the construction of`
  line `buildings on land adjoining such monument and the removal of unauthorised buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) the grant of licences and permissions to make excavations for archaeological purposes in`
  line `protected areas, the authorities by whom, and the restrictions and conditions subject to which,`
  line `such licences may be granted, the taking of securities from licensees and the fees that may be`
  line `charged for such licensees;`
  line
  line `(c) the right of access of the public to a protected monument and the fee, if any, to be charged`
  line therefore;
  line
  line `^1[(ca) the categories of ancient monuments or archaeological sites and remains, declared as of`
  line `national importance, under sub-section (1) of section 4A;`
  line
  line `(cb) the manner of making application for grant of permission under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20D;`
  line
  line `(cc) the category of applications in respect of which the permission may be granted and`
  line `applications which shall be referred to the Authority for its recommendation, under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 20D;`
  line
  line `(cd) the other matters including heritage controls such as elevations, facades, drainage`
  line `systems, roads and service infrastructure (including electric poles, water and sewer pipelines)`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 20E;`
  line
  line `(ce) the manner of preparation of detailed site plans in respect of each prohibited area and`
  line `regulated area and the time within which such heritage bye-laws shall be prepared and particulars`
  line `to be included in each such heritage bye-laws under sub-section (3) of section 20E;`
  line
  line `(cf) salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the`
  line `whole-time Chairperson and whole-time members, or fees or allowances payable to the part-time`
  line `members, of the Authority under sub-section (1) of section 20H;`
  line
  line `(cg) the form in which and time at which the Authority shall prepare an annual report giving`
  line `full description of its activities for the previous year under section 20P;`
  line
  line `(ch) the form and manner in which the Authority and competent authority shall furnish`
  line `information to the Central Government under section 20Q;]`
  line
  line `(d) the form and contents of the report of an archaeological officer or a licensee under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which applications for permission under section 19 or section 25 may be made`
  line `and the particulars which they should contain;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and manner of preferring appeals under this Act and the time within which they`
  line `may be preferred;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of service of any order or notice under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which excavations and other like operations for archaeological purposes`
  line `may be carried on;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rule made under this section may provide that a breach thereof shall be punishable,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a rule made with reference to clause (a) of sub-section (2), with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a rule made with reference to clause (b) of sub-section (2), with fine which`
  line `may extend to five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of a rule made with reference to clause (c) of sub-section (2), with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 2010, s. 11 (w.e.f. 16-6-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (34764)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 63
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310&sectionId=34764&sectionno=39&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_27_37_00002_195824_1517807319310
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ancient and Historical Monuments and Archaeological Sites`
  line `and Remains (Declaration of National Importance) Act, 1951 (71 of 1951), and section 126 of the`
  line `States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ancient Monuments Preservation Act, 1904 (7 of 1904), shall cease to have effect in`
  line `relation to ancient and historical monuments and archaeological sites and remains declared by or`
  line `under this Act to be of national importance, except as respects things done or omitted to be done`
  line `before the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
